00:46:41.500 --> 00:46:45.130
And I would love to
hear, what can we do?

00:46:45.130 --> 00:46:47.320
What can I do, and
what is possible to do

00:46:47.320 --> 00:46:52.210
within this really ridiculously
complicated and totally unequal

00:46:52.210 --> 00:46:54.820
system of resources of people?

00:46:54.820 --> 00:46:57.010
And where can we get
more people like you

00:46:57.010 --> 00:46:59.560
to take the place of
principals that berate teachers

00:46:59.560 --> 00:47:02.260
and an administration that
doesn't feel like they

00:47:02.260 --> 00:47:03.064
want to engage.

00:47:03.064 --> 00:47:04.480
NADIA LOPEZ: So
ironically enough,

00:47:04.480 --> 00:47:08.986
my teaching experience
started in Fort Greene.

00:47:08.986 --> 00:47:10.360
And that's why I
