00:47:14.440 --> 00:47:15.670
So it starts with leadership.

00:47:15.670 --> 00:47:15.880
Right?

00:47:15.880 --> 00:47:17.950
Leadership sets the tone,
and it was the leader.

00:47:17.950 --> 00:47:20.730
And then, there were
just people who, I feel,

00:47:20.730 --> 00:47:24.910
were the little cronies who
felt like the only way we can

00:47:24.910 --> 00:47:27.490
survive is to be the same way.

00:47:27.490 --> 00:47:30.840
And it was so toxic.

00:47:30.840 --> 00:47:33.280
So I'm going to tell you
that after three years,

00:47:33.280 --> 00:47:34.600
I had to leave.

00:47:34.600 --> 00:47:36.220
I wanted to leave
the first year,

00:47:36.220 --> 00:47:38.260
but it was before
they made changes

00:47:38.260 --> 00:47:39.370
that allowed us to leave.

00:47:39.370 --> 00:47:42.160
Like, we literally
were held captive,

00:47:42.160 --> 00:47:47.590
and it required the chancellor
to let you leave the school.

00:47:47.590 --> 00:47:52.970
As a parent, as a
community, and as a person

00:47:52.970 --> 00:47:57.130
who lives in the community,
you can share your concerns

00:47:57.130 --> 00:47:58.630
with the superintendent.

00:47:58.630 --> 00:48:03.550
You can share your
concerns by calling 311.

00:48:03.550 --> 00:48:06.520
Part of it is, if they
don't know what's going on,

00:48:06.520 --> 00:48:08.440
nothing will ever change.

00:48:08.440 --> 00:48:10.750
I feel like as a
principal, I hold myself

00:48:10.750 --> 00:48:11.740
to the highest regard.

00:48:11.740 --> 00:48:16.990
Sometimes, it's to a detriment,
because if a paper didn't

00:48:16.990 --> 00:48:19.320
go home on Monday, and
it ends up on Tuesday,

00:48:19.320 --> 00:48:21.070
parents are like, we
didn't get the paper.

00:48:21.070 --> 00:48:22.070
We didn't get the paper.

00:48:22.070 --> 00:48:23.350
And I'm like, it's a paper.

00:48:23.350 --> 00:48:24.250
Right?

00:48:24.250 --> 00:48:26.110
But in other schools,
if it's something

00:48:26.110 --> 00:48:29.400
like kids feeling like
they've been demoralized,

00:48:29.400 --> 00:48:30.775
they've been shut
out of classes,

00:48:30.775 --> 00:48:34.060
and they've been thrown out of
classes, they don't speak up.

00:48:34.060 --> 00:48:35.830
And it's often because
of the retaliation

00:48:35.830 --> 00:48:38.410
that they feel is going to come.

00:48:38.410 --> 00:48:43.150
But you on the outside
can speak to that.

00:48:43.150 --> 00:48:45.580
There's always someone
willing to listen.

00:48:45.580 --> 00:48:49.000
It has to start with actually
telling and making that call.

00:48:49.000 --> 00:48:54.790
So the options are,
311 and superintendent.

00:48:54.790 --> 00:48:57.312
Those are your best options,
because anything else is not

00:48:57.312 --> 00:48:58.270
going to make a change.

00:48:58.270 --> 00:48:59.350
You're not going to
go into the school.

00:48:59.350 --> 00:49:01.660
The principal's not
going to listen to you.

00:49:01.660 --> 00:49:04.237
But those people hold
them accountable.

00:49:04.237 --> 00:49:05.570
SPEAKER: Can I do one follow-up?

00:49:05.570 --> 00:49:06.278
NADIA LOPEZ: Yes.

00:49:06.278 --> 00:49:09.110
SPEAKER: What if it's been
